        "created_at": "2020-03-31T22:23:53.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Opened the 2000 Vincent Girardin Clos de la Roche.  Dark red but almost brick color, a quick taste was tart with little fruit.  Decanted for 30 minutes and then revisited.  Fruit woke-up: strawberry, leather, and some darker fruit which is becoming more pronounced over the meal.  Balanced and the finish continues to improve.  Still a level of freshness while it adds weight.  Very enjoyable.</p>",
